  "body": "In Ethereum Studio (www.ether.camp) RPC address looks like this:\nhttps://zduniak.by.ether.camp:8555/sandbox/78d7ffca53\nFrom what I see there is no way to configure rpc in truffle.js so that the HttpProvider has '/sandbox/78d7ffca53' sufix in the url (I can specify only host and port, not the whole path)\n\nIs there a way to configure truffle with this sort of sufixes in the RPC url ?\n",
